Below is a **self‑contained, minimal‑but‑functional** implementation of a small library system.  
It consists of three public classes:

| Class | Responsibility | Key fields | Key methods |
|-------|-----------------|------------|-------------|
| **Book** | Represents a catalog item. | `id`, `title`, `author`, `available` | `checkout()`, `checkin()`, `toString()` |
| **Member** | Represents a borrower. | `id`, `name`, `borrowedBooks` | `borrow(Book)`, `returnBook(Book)`, `toString()` |
| **Library** | Manages books & members, and orchestrates book loans. | `books`, `members` | `addBook(...)`, `registerMember(...)`, `loanBook(...)`, `returnBook(...)`, `searchBooks(...)`, `listAvailableBooks()` |

> **Note** – This is only a demo; it keeps all data in RAM and does not persist it to disk. For a real‑world project you would want a database, proper concurrency handling, persistence, security, etc.

