## 1. `Book.java`

```java
package library;

import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;

/**
 * Represents an immutable book in the library catalog.
 */
public final class Book {
    private static final AtomicInteger idGenerator = new AtomicInteger(1);

    private final int id;          // unique identifier
    private final String title;
    private final String author;
    private boolean available;     // true if the book is in the library

    public Book(String title, String author) {
        this.id = idGenerator.getAndIncrement();
        this.title = title;
        this.author = author;
        this.available = true;     // new books are initially available
    }

    /* ---------- Getters ---------- */

    public int getId() { return id; }
    public String getTitle() { return title; }
    public String getAuthor() { return author; }
    public boolean isAvailable() { return available; }

    /* ---------- State changes ---------- */

    /**
     * Marks the book as checked out. Causes {@code IllegalStateException}
     * if the book has already been checked out.
     */
    void checkout() {
        if (!available) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Book " + id + " already checked out.");
        }
        available = false;
    }

    /**
     * Marks the book as returned. Causes {@code IllegalStateException}
     * if the book was not checked out.
     */
    void checkin() {
        if (available) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Book " + id + " not checked out.");
        }
        available = true;
    }

    /* ---------- Object overrides ---------- */

    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return String.format("Book[id=%d, title=\"%s\", author=\"%s\", %s]",
                id, title, author, available ? "Available" : "Checked out");
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Integer.hashCode(id);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object obj) {
        return (obj instanceof Book) && ((Book)obj).id == this.id;
    }
}
```

